## Why join AP-LS?

The American Psychology-Law Society (AP-LS) is an interdisciplinary organization devoted to scholarship, practice, and public service in psychology and law. AP-LS is both a free-standing organization as well as a division (Division 41) of the American Psychological Association (APA). Membership in AP-LS is therefore separate and independent from membership in Division 41 of APA, although many members belong to both organizations (AP-LS and APA).

Membership is open to interested professionals and students in other disciplines beyond psychology. AP-LS membership is for the calendar year January 1 - December 31. To join or renew your membership, please visit our membership management page.

<a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="https://apls.memberclicks.net/membership-form#!/" role="button">Become a Member</a>

### Membership Benefits

The activities of AP-LS in its brief history have been quite diverse, including developing a collection of course syllabi and teaching materials, conducting a survey of career opportunities in psychology and law, studying special ethical problems in expert testimony, drafting recommendations, and sponsoring an annual conference as well as programming at APA.

